          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Measured cross sections were corrected for:",
                "1. Multiple scattering and self-shielding effects:",
                "  ---------------------------------------------------",
                "    En (keV)       C1                    C2",
                "  ---------------------------------------------------",
                " Thermal maxw      0.97230               1.0562",
                "     425           0.99995               1.0295",
                "     480           0.99995               1.0305",
                "     535           0.99995               1.0310",
                "     590           0.99995               1.0313",
                "     615           0.99995               1.0316",
                "     645           0.99996               1.0319",
                "     690           0.99996               1.0321",
                "     740           0.99996               1.0325",
                "     845           0.99996               1.0333",
                "     950           0.99997               1.0338",
                "  ------------ --------------------------------------",
                "   C1: Self-shielding + multiple scattering correction",
                "       factor for Al-foils",
                "   C2: Multiple scattering correction factor for Th-",
                "       pellet",
                "2. The effect of the variation of neutron flux as a",
                "   function of time was taken into consideration.",
                "   This correction factor was found to be less than 6%.",
                "3. Second group of neutrons due Ep > 2.4 MeV the",
                "   estimated error due to this  corr  < +/- 1%.",
                "4. The average energy and the spread of the neutron",
                "   beam for Li target thickness. The neutron spread",
                "   due this was calcu. to be varying from +/-15 to",
                "   +/- 25 keV",
                "5. The energy spread due to the angular spread of",
                "   neutrons. This was estimated to be about +/- 17 keV."
              ]
            }
          ],
